<subSubSection id="2563AD0BF13616CB79E0287D79381D34" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="description">
<paragraph id="10FB5B52D04398C3ACDA88BEC11ABA41" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Generic characters.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="653BE4A9FA1E117A78BFD940BF741951" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
The generic characters of 
<taxonomicName id="72683E2533BC8B7D3E3AD100E96CC515" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="49EAB787CF6F6FB24FD99B08BB199CB6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its differentiation from related genera are detailed in 
<bibRefCitation id="314949EDC691A4C679AE6F80AD1105CE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" author="Wilkinson, C" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Zoological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="407 - 517" refId="B26" refString="Wilkinson, C, 1968. A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae). Transactions of the Zoological Society of London 31 (4): 407 - 517, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" title="A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" volume="31" year="1968">Wilkinson (1968)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="74253FDE873CF3923976283241C99448" author="Jiang, S" journalOrPublisher="Entomotaxonomia" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="81 - 88" refId="B12" refString="Jiang, S, Han, HX, 2019. A new species of Ditrigona Moore (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae) in China, with a checklist to the triangularia -group. Entomotaxonomia 41 (2): 81 - 88" title="A new species of Ditrigona Moore (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae) in China, with a checklist to the triangularia - group." volume="41" year="2019">Jiang and Han (2019)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="092CC76BF57EDE4C8EDECB4FA24792D1" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="2AEEDCA66F12A21A0CE90C50210C083C" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8ABEAE53FFCA4B4BCC07FDFF40A43B4A" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
The species of 
<taxonomicName id="AE054205BC695BF980649516D3932663" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9683D970391CA59742E43D73BF4AAA13" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are mainly distributed in the Oriental region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E1BC7FDE33833F589B73875B05BEE039" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="derocina species group">
<paragraph id="7CB24695DBCB6AE0360FEBA1A17DDE54" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<taxonomicName id="DD6A725B5A2C5E5721950C0436E66D33" baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona derocina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derocina">
<emphasis id="6443619EF33DB870FEB4B8D984E5DB2E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona derocina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8119D8461662EE43AE981D9239EB115C" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<bibRefCitation id="5911746106DA993BA877EADC2A03BC1A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" author="Wilkinson, C" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Zoological Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="407 - 517" refId="B26" refString="Wilkinson, C, 1968. A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae). Transactions of the Zoological Society of London 31 (4): 407 - 517, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" title="A Taxonomic revision of the genus Ditrigona (Lepidoptera: Drepanidae: Drepaninae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1096-3642.1968.tb00369.x" volume="31" year="1968">Wilkinson (1968)</bibRefCitation>
placed three species in the 
<taxonomicName id="8437073397A15E3566F216D7BD8485D4" baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona derocina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derocina">
<emphasis id="BD564BE0398CA451BFE9BBC058444EEE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona derocina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group: 
<taxonomicName id="136168E0D0B57568D4FB13641EEA7988" baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona derocina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derocina">
<emphasis id="0B6E81499A1E11941618E1FC4155DBDE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona derocina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bryk), 
<taxonomicName id="62A5F85805BB162494456EFDEFA8FBCB" authorityName="Wilkinson" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona diana" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diana">
<emphasis id="AA2AC10F487C2E830A07C20F723A6B45" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona diana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wilkinson, and 
<taxonomicName id="7615BAF2C1AF304C1FE0ED8C1BFBDA71" baseAuthorityName="Moore" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona pruinosa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pruinosa">
<emphasis id="33504E1BE97AF983CC5D2E49D816BFF4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona pruinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Moore). The two former species have been recorded in China, and a further species, 
<taxonomicName id="431C55AC72641D5EF41FFBBA355FEFEB" authorityName="Guo &amp; Cheng &amp; Jiang &amp; Xue &amp; Han" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Guo &amp; Cheng &amp; Jiang &amp; Xue &amp; Han" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Deroca" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deroca crystalla" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crystalla">
<emphasis id="14B2D66903669177396EC67D1E5F755D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Deroca crystalla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Chu &amp; Wang, 1987 is newly placed in this species group in this work.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9BBE8C3070E72BFFCBF139C82DE6DF6A" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
Species of the 
<taxonomicName id="C1D20AF88B7E2773FFF84364753ACC65" baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona derocina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derocina">
<emphasis id="DC4A619095AA63E365899FF40FD16464" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona derocina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group are characterized by unipectinate antennae and semi-transparent wings. In the male genitalia, the 
<taxonomicName id="0BB06BF0372385102945EDB4EB4289CC" baseAuthorityName="Bryk" baseAuthorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona derocina" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="derocina">
<emphasis id="EE2C3D231F6CBFF2D8CEB877280F83D9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona derocina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group is unusual in 
<taxonomicName id="95ADBC46A60ABDF04767D518E3E65902" authorityName="Moore" authorityYear="1888" class="Insecta" family="Drepanidae" genus="Ditrigona" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ditrigona" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0D1EDACC98D6F0A2DBB4065A52DFA935" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Ditrigona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having sclerotization of the vinculum, and a quite long and narrow aedeagus. The eighth sternite is distinguished by large and curved octavals, and the tergite protrudes strongly. The female genitalia are characterized by having a very long ductus bursae, an ostial plate, an accessory sac and a long and narrow signum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
